      • implement

        public void implement(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Description copied from interface: Impler
        Produces code implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added. Generated source code should be placed in the correct subdirectory of the specified root directory and have correct file name. For example, the implementation of the interface List should go to $root/java/util/ListImpl.java

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - when implementation cannot be generated.

      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Gets console argument and executes implementation. Two mode is possible:
        • 2 arguments: className rootPath - call implement(Class, Path) with given arguments. It's generate implementation of class or interface
        • 3 arguments: -jar className jarPath - call implementJar(Class, Path) with two last arguments. It's generate jar file with implementation of class or interface.
        If arguments are incorrect or an error occurs during implementation returns message with information about error.
        Parameters:
        args - arguments for running an application.
